==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: canopic jar
<hw>ca*no"pic jar`</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a jar used in ancient
Egyptian tombs to contain the intestines of a person who was mummified
for burial; -- also called <altname>canopic vase</altname>.</def>
<altsp>[Also spelled <asp>Canopic jar</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>canopied</ent>⟦br⟧
